parameters: Clea: Guild Master, it seems like you're okay...

Guild Master Agonia: It seems that I can't win against age
when it comes to letting someone escape.

Organization thug: Hii... B-brother, we're gonna get killed,
Cors' brother, let's escape quickly!

Cors the Wanderer: As expected, everyone from the renowned
Adventurer's Guild in the Empire, I am Cors. Around here, I
go by the name Cors the Wanderer.

Cors the Wanderer: Well, please take a seat. We can't have a
proper discussion if you're standing, right?

Guild Master Agonia: Clea, this is Lesson 1. In a match like
this, you should try to take control of the pace.

Guild Master Agonia: Now, naturally, you're ordering us to
sit down.
Clea: Yes. So, what should I do?

Guild Master Agonia: Ignore it. Completely ignore it.
Without listening to the other party's words, do it
thoroughly.

Guild Master Agonia: To extract information, one person is
enough. The entourage is troublesome, so make them all keep
quiet.

Organization Thug: Tch, I won't just let myself be beaten
for free!!

Guild Leader Agonia: Well, it seems like everything is
settled. So, do you have any requests for us?

Cors the Wanderer: Oh my, it's the Death God, the Assassin,
and the Executioner Agonia... The rumors were true, huh?

Cors the Wanderer: Would you please have a seat? I humbly
request a favor.

Guild Leader Agonia: Hmm, very well. Clea, please stand
guard at the exit.

Guild Leader Agonia: Please tell me about the relationship
between the traitorous client and the merchant Acreo.
Guild Leader Agonia: I see, so Acreo requested an escort.

Cors the Wanderer: Well, you see, he is not only a high-
ranking client of the organization, but I didn't know he had
betrayed the guild.

Cors the Wanderer: In the sense that the organization
doesn't want to antagonize the Adventurer's Guild, we also
feel like victims.

Guild Leader Agonia: Hmm... I see. Clea, please head towards
Acreo's shop.
Clea: Understood. What about the Guild Leader?

Guild Leader Agonia: I have some business to attend to with
him, so I will head to Acreo's shop later. Let's meet there.

Cors the Wanderer: To think that I would end up going on a
date with such beautiful young ladies like this... as the
Death God...

Cors the Wanderer: Well, since I have considered the
destination, I will guide you there.

Cors the Wanderer: Ladies of the Adventurer's Guild, what
brings you here today?

Clea: Today, we came as messengers from the Magic Academy,
sent by Dokusa-san.

Cors the Wanderer: Hehehe, you certainly have a wide circle
of friends. Well then, shall we discuss the request?

Cors the Wanderer: Do you know about a place called the
Great Rock Castle near Mucos?

Mage Relm: Of course, I know about it! It's a group that
conducts independent magical research, right?

Mage Relm: It's a facility with history, but compared to the
Magic Academy, it's nothing special!

Cors the Wanderer: It seems that our organization has had a
long-standing relationship with them, but it has become
quite troublesome.

Cors the Wanderer: We dispatched several skilled
individuals, but they were all defeated and it has become
quite troublesome.

Priestess Sophia: For everyone who values their comrades,
that is a problem that cannot be ignored.

Cors the Wanderer: Indeed, you are absolutely right... It's
a bit of a headache, you see.

Cors the Wanderer: The name of the monster is the daughter
of one of the clans of the Great Rock Castle, Anat.
Clea: The request is to defeat Anat, is that correct?

Cors the Wanderer: That's right, but please make sure not to
kill her.

Cors the Wanderer: I have posted a request on the bulletin
board, so if you can officially accept it, please let me
know.

Cors the Wanderer: Today... thanks to everyone's easy-to-
understand faces, we were able to protect the organization's
reputation, right?

Cors the Wanderer: I added some color to the reward, so I am
grateful for this job.
Clea: Thank you very much. We will take our leave now.

Cors the Wanderer: Wait a moment, I have personally decided
to trust all of you.

Cors the Wanderer: It's a job with a bit of a special
circumstance... but if you're willing to cooperate, please
accept it on the bulletin board.
Clea: Understood, thank you very much.

Cors the Wanderer: Hehe, I'll continue to rely on you all
from now on.
実績 衣をまといて魔女になる

Cors the Wanderer: Please take care of the request to become
the witch of the Great Rock Castle and help the
organization's members.

Cors the Wanderer: It's a matter of reputation, so please
help us out.

Cors the Wanderer: As expected of everyone from the
Adventurer's Guild, if there are any special jobs, please
count on me again.

Cors the Wanderer: You all are capable of completing any
requests, as expected.
Cors the Wanderer: Do you have a problem you need help with?
Clea: Yes, it's a really troublesome problem.

Cors the Wanderer: Ahaha, please go easy on me with your
request.

Cors the Wanderer: Goblins, orcs, dragons... Are you telling
me these stories for some other purpose?
Clea: It's true, please help us.

Cors the Wanderer: Th-this is no joke, you know. It won't
bring me any money, and it won't fill my belly with honor,
you know.

Sophia the Priestess: I will assist you when you are in
trouble... That was the condition for finding the man with
the knife tattoo, right?

Priestess Sophia: Or perhaps, Cors-san, who does business
based on trust, will not keep his promise with us?
Cors the Wanderer: W-Well, that may be true, but...
Priestess Sophia: Alright, let's give up on Cors-san.

Priestess Sophia: Even if there is a coward, they will only
be a hindrance... isn't that right?
Clea: Yes, you're in the way.

Cors the Wanderer: Sigh... What should I do to cooperate for
the sake of everyone with such a reckless negotiation
tactic?

Clea: I don't expect much from Cors-san's fighting ability.
Even if they're just mercenaries, please bring some fighting
force.

Cors the Wanderer: Alright, alright, I got it. After this is
over, please help me with a really troublesome job, okay?
Priestess Sophia: Oh my, do you think we will win?

Cors the Wanderer: Well, you see, I can't eat it no matter
how it's cooked, ahaha. The dragon is really unfortunate,
isn't it?

Cors the Wanderer: I'll head to the site with the
mercenaries... sigh... I also need to think of excuses for
the higher-ups in the organization.

bro says studying numbers is important, you know...

Cors the Wanderer: Miss... by any chance, did you accept a
request from the general store Libra?
Clea: Yes, is there a problem?

Cors the Wanderer: I may not be the one to say this as
someone who runs an office... but those guys from Libra are
quite experienced and cunning, you know.

Cors the Wanderer: It's better not to get involved more than
necessary.

Cors the Wanderer: Merchants... they're the ones who make

Cors the Wanderer: Please be careful, okay?

Organization thug: 'Sometimes the boss disappears out of the
blue. Maybe he's off somewhere with a mistress.'

Organization thug: 'I've heard about all of you, so please
stay at that table and relax!'

Thief Nora: Does pretending to be a prostitute mean that
you're a woman?

Mage Relm: I don't know about that! It could also be a
possibility of a small male using magic to create an
illusion.

Captain Clevo: Who is that guy, Cors? If he was able to take
my first strike, he must be someone with combat experience.

Priestess Sophia: I can't say it out loud, but he's a thug
affiliated with the Mucos organization.

Organization thug: Indeed, my boss is a no-good thug, but
he's a brave man who made great contributions in the naval
battle against the neighboring country Tarasa!

Priestess Sophia: I'm not sure if you're complimenting me,
but by the way, do you have any decent wine?

Captain Clevo: Are you back from the naval battle... just
like us?
Thief Nora: Captain, you don't seem well. Are you okay?

Captain Clevo: For the Emma Thief Guild, the sea was like
hell, so there was also a desire to return to our homeland,
Camps...

Captain Clevo: After going through that naval battle, which
made us want to stay away from the sea more than anything, I
sincerely respect those who continue to stay by the sea.
Organization thug: T-The Delya Dagger has appeared!
Clea: Do you know where he went?

Organization thug: Probably a slum for the defeated

delivered!

Clea: Let's definitely solve it. It's the only thing we can
do for that child.

Cors the Wanderer: If you say that, I'll believe you. It
seems like it's going to be a challenging job.
Cors the Wanderer: Haha, looks like I'm quite disliked, huh?

Cors the Wanderer: I found out during my investigation of
the organization that a nobleman 【kept】 Deirei's dagger.

Cors the Wanderer: I have informed the leader of the thieves
about it. I will be heading to Dromos now, but what should I
do?

Thief Nora: I really dislike you, but I'll go with you for
the sake of that child.

Clea: Cors-san, are you also going for revenge on behalf of
our comrades?

Cors the Wanderer: I'm different, you know. For members of
the organization, even dying is part of the job.

Cors the Wanderer: This is a job, you know. That's why I'll
definitely settle the score.
